#Text=Melbourne
#Text=Melbourne
#Text=is the second largest city and the cultural capital of Australia , with Victorian-era architecture , extensive shopping , museums , galleries , theatres , and large parks and gardens .
#Text=Many of its 5 million residents are both multicultural and sports-mad .

#Text=The capital of the south-eastern state of Victoria , and located at the head of Port Phillip Bay , Melbourne is a magnet for migrants from all over the world , and consistently ranks as one of the world 's most liveable cities .

#Text=Visitors come to attend major sporting events , and to use it as a base for exploring nearby places such as Grampians National Park , the Great Ocean Road , and Phillip Island and its penguin parade .
#Text=Many UK visitors come for tours of filming locations of the soap opera Neighbours .
#Text=History
#Text=The British settlement of Melbourne commenced in 1835 when settlers from Tasmania " purchased " land on Port Phillip Bay and the Yarra River from the local Aboriginal people .
#Text=The streets of central Melbourne were carefully laid out in 1837 , with some streets 30 metres wide .
#Text=The settlement was named " Melbourne " after William Lamb , 2nd Viscount Melbourne , the British Prime Minister at that time .
#Text=The first British lieutenant-governor , Charles La Trobe , arrived in 1839 – his Cottage still stands and can be visited in the Kings Domain .
#Text=1851 was a landmark for Melbourne — the colony of Victoria was separated from New South Wales and very soon after , gold was discovered in Victoria , sparking a huge gold rush .
#Text=The gold rush history can be seen at the Gold Treasury Museum , housed in the Treasury Building built in 1858 .
#Text=Gold was the catalyst for several decades of prosperity lasting through to the late 1880s and examples of the ornate Victorian-era structures built during this time still stand .
#Text=Throughout the gold and building booms , Melbourne managed to retain its many spacious parks and gardens that remain to this day .
#Text=In 1888 , the boom collapsed and Victoria suffered through the depression of the 1890s .

#Text=In 1901 , the British colonies of Australia federated and Melbourne became the temporary capital of Australia , with the Federal Parliament meeting in the Parliament House of Victoria until 1927 when the new Federal capital of Canberra was founded .
#Text=After World War II , Melbourne grew rapidly , with its mainly Anglo-Celtic population boosted by immigration from Europe , particularly from Greece and Italy .
#Text=Today Melbourne has the biggest Greek population ( over 800,000 ) of any city outside Greece and the biggest Italian population ( over 230,000 ) of any city outside Italy .
#Text=The significant pre-war Jewish population was also boosted after the war .
#Text=From the mid-1970s , many immigrants came from Southeast Asia , particularly Vietnam and Cambodia .
#Text=Melbourne has had a Chinese population since the gold rush of the 1850s .
#Text=Chinatown has existed from that time but the population of Chinese and other East Asians has also been boosted by immigration .
#Text=New highrise buildings replaced many of Melbourne ’s interesting old structures in the construction boom of the 1970s and 80s .
#Text=Melbournians belatedly recognised the loss of their architectural heritage and steps were taken to protect what was left .
#Text=Construction of the huge Crown Casino ( briefly the largest casino in the world ) in the 1990s introduced glitz and gambling to the city centre .
#Text=Melbourne ’s development continues in the 2000s with the opening of the Melbourne Museum , Federation Square and the Docklands precinct .
#Text=Culture

#Text=Melbourne is the cultural capital of Australia , with its many art galleries , film festivals , orchestras , choral and opera productions , vibrant live music scene , and a strong food , wine and coffee culture .
#Text=People in Melbourne tend to dress up more than the northern states - partly due to the colder climate .
#Text=Many bars and clubs have strict dress regulations , such as requiring collars and dress shoes for men .
#Text=Particular cultural events to note include the Melbourne International Film Festival in August , the International Art Festival in October , and the Melbourne Comedy Festival in April .
#Text=There are also many concerts and exhibitions throughout the year .

#Text=In addition to the Melbourne Museum , there are special museums dedicated to subjects such as science , immigration , Chinese history , Jewish history , sport , racing , film and moving image , railways , police , fire brigades and banking .
#Text=Sport
#Text=Melbournians are sports enthusiasts and particularly passionate about Australian rules football , a sport invented in Melbourne .
#Text=In fact the Australian Football League ( AFL ) is not so much a sport as a religion in Melbourne , with 9 of the 10 Victorian teams being based in Melbourne .
#Text=As a guide , the entire national competition only has 18 teams , meaning half the league is based in Melbourne alone .
#Text=The AFL culminates in the AFL Grand Final in the spring , which is played every year at the Melbourne Cricket Ground .

#Text=Horse racing is another passion , and the majority of the state has a public holiday on the first Tuesday of November for the racing of the Melbourne Cup , one of the world ’s famous horse races .
#Text=Cricket is the big summer sport and the Melbourne Cricket Ground ( the ' MCG ' ) is one of the world 's leading grounds .
#Text=The National Sports Museum ( NSM ) ( including the Racing Museum ) Australia ’s only truly dedicated multi-sports museum is also located at the MCG .
#Text=Each January , Melbourne hosts tennis ' Australian Open , one of the world ’s four Grand Slam championships .
#Text=In March , Melbourne hosts the first race of the Formula One season , the Formula One Grand Prix .
#Text=The race is held in Albert Park in South Melbourne .

#Text=Two professional Association Football teams are based in Melbourne , Melbourne Victory and Melbourne City FC ; the two teams now share the new Melbourne Rectangular Stadium , commercially known as AAMI Park also playing at Etihad Stadium .
#Text=The city also boasts one professional team in each rugby code , with both also playing at AAMI Park .
#Text=The Melbourne Storm play rugby league in the National Rugby League , with teams throughout Australia plus one in New Zealand .
#Text=The Melbourne Rebels play rugby union in Super Rugby , which features four other Australian sides and five each in New Zealand and South Africa .

#Text=Melbourne is the unquestioned sporting capital of Australia with the largest arenas and two of the major sporting administrations basing their operation in Melbourne : Cricket Australia is a stone 's throw from the MCG , and the AFL games are played at both the MCG and Etihad Stadium .
